newsitem.title: FINLAND: Finnish GDP advanced to 5.7 pct in October.
newsitem.headline: Finnish GDP advanced to 5.7 pct in October.

text.p: Growth in Finland's gross domestic product accelerated to 5.7 percent year-on-year in October from 4.2 percent in September, Statistics Finland said in a statement on Tuesday.
Adjusted for seasonal factors, GDP rose 0.4 percent in October on September, SF said.
Production increased in all the main industrial sectors in October.
Forestry and agricultural production rose almost eight percent year-on-year, SF said.
Industrial output adjusted for work days increased by almost seven percent year-on-year, it said.
Building output grew 6.5 percent and production in wholesale and retail trade rose almost 7.5 percent, SF said.
Transport sector output rose almost eight percent on the year-ago level, it said. Output of other services and of the public sector rose two percent, SF said.
